				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Crypt of Nadox a Hot Zone?!?!?  Not for Me!<a name="37766"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 3 04 12:38 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I went to Hate's Fury as my 56 cleric with a full group of mid - high 50's, a good dps group with good players. First of all, the trip to get to Hate's Fury is not pleasent, to say the least. At first we tried to plow our way there from Nadox but it took us seemingly forever to kill each mob (either dps was not as good as I thought, or mobs have godly hp) and they were giving 1% every 3 kill or so. So we opted to just make a mad dash to the Hate's Fury zone (see invis mobs here and there). Everyone made it except the bard.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, we started in Hate's Fury finally, exp is still about 1% per 3 kills. Pulling single wasn't too hard. Adds were mez'ed by bard farily easily. We were planning to plow around the ship just to explore but on a bad pull, my cleric got nuked to death by 3 nuker mobs before I could finish casting a quick heal on my self. Group evac'ed to &quot;safe point&quot;, which was in middle of 5 mobs, couple of them died.
<br />

<br />
I had to log on my bard, run there, tried to drag corpse but figured out there is a GY, which was in middle of 5 mobs... I had to use bard to clear the 5 mobs and switched to cleric for rez.
<br />

<br />
Why do they make the evac point and GY in middle of 5 mobs is beyond me; just unecessary headach for the players.
<br />

<br />
I thought I got about 10% exp in about 2 hours (including travel time, rez time etc). This same group could get 10% exp in less than 30 mins in PoP. Althought it was fun, since it was the first time for the group to visit that zone, nobody in group wanted to stay longer nor give it another visit any time soon.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
